-- China Shineway Rises to Record in Hong Kong Trading on DBS Vickers Rating
-- Stanley James
-- 2010-06-15T04:31:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-15/china-shineway-rises-to-record-in-hong-kong-trading-on-dbs-vickers-rating.html

          
          
             China Shineway Pharmaceutical Group
Ltd. rose to a record in Hong Kong trading today after the
stock’s rating was changed to “buy” from “hold” by DBS
Vickers analyst Gideon Lo.  
 The stock soared 10 percent to HK$27.55 as of the midday
break on the city’s stock exchange, the highest level since
listing in December 2004. The shares gained as much as 13
percent earlier today.  
          
          


  


        